content:
Geo maps allow you to visualize data that contains geographical coordinates (latitude and longitude). 

A dataset with geographical location data can be overlaid on a map. The bubbles representing a measure appear centered on the state areas.

Create a Geo Map Chart

To create a geo map chart, add a dataset with geographical location data. The locations should have latitude and longitude coordinates to visualize the data accurately.

Example:

Airport, Year, Quarter, Lat, Lng, Flights, Passengers
JFK, 2014, 1, 40.639751, -73.778925, 120000, 67276

In the lens, click and select the Geo Map chart type. Select the map type (e.g., US States) and location field that determines where to add bubbles.

Add two measures: average latitude coordinates and average longitude coordinates. Add a measure for bubble size and another for bubble color.

To make additional changes, set the chart properties in the Formatting panel.
